From f5aaca08f000a4368f280bba960a09443f2ac9df Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sai Rupesh Chevuru <chevuru@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Sep 2025 15:57:54 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:DP:wifi:ath12k: Skip dp_peer cleanup for non AP VAPs
 during recovery

During recovery scenarios currently we iterates over all vaps to perform dp_peer cleanup.
However, it has been observed that in certain cases, monitor VAPs are assigned
the same MAC address as regular AP VAPs. This overlap is leading to unintended
AP bss peer cleanup during recovery. Since non AP VAPs do not create dp_peer
attempting to clean them up is unnecessary and potentially harmful.
To address this, recovery logic is updated to skip dp_peer cleanup for non AP VAPs.

Patch-Dependency:
	0344-0002-QSDK-CP-wifi-ath12k-Add-support-for-Mode-1-recovery-.patch
	0478-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Add-API-for-ath12k_dp_peer-s.patch

Fixes:
	Ibce6428a4(QSDK:CP: wifi: ath12k: Add Mode-1 recovery support)

Signed-off-by: Sai Rupesh Chevuru <chevuru@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index e1db29c..6ae05b6 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -1514,8 +1514,10 @@ void ath12k_mac_peer_cleanup_all(struct ath12k *ar)
 	/* Delete all the self dp_peers on asserted radio
 	 */
 	list_for_each_entry_safe_reverse(arvif, tmp_vif, &ar->arvifs, list) {
-		ath12k_dp_peer_delete(dp_hw, arvif->bssid, NULL);
-		arvif->num_stations = 0;
+		if (arvif->ahvif->vdev_type == WMI_VDEV_TYPE_AP) {
+			ath12k_dp_peer_delete(dp_hw, arvif->bssid, NULL);
+			arvif->num_stations = 0;
+		}
 	}
 
 	ath12k_dbg_level(ar->ab, ATH12K_DBG_MAC, ATH12K_DBG_L2,
-- 
